description:
Synq does not compile because the current jdk8 javac thinks the various methods' parameter types in Event.java (and others) are too ambiguous.

Ex:

``` java
    default <R> PollEvent<T> failIf(R item, Predicate<? super R> predicate) {
        return failIf(() -> item, predicate);
    }

    default <R> PollEvent<T> failIf(Callable<R> item, Predicate<? super R> predicate) {
        return failIf(Condition.match(item, predicate));
    }
```

Eclipse compiler seems to interpret the intention here just fine. but I can see how javac thinks it is ambiguous. R could also be interpreted as a Callable itself, so, it is perhaps too generic.

The solution is probably to get rid of the R item version, and if a specific object reference is needed to be looked up at every event evaluation then it will be up to the user to simply call the second form with the lambda, "() -> item".

