description:
Working off master.

I have a java method as part of the teavm port.

```
    public InputStream getStream(String url){
        if (!isMediaResource(url)){
            return getArrayBufferInputStream(url);
        } 
        return new MediaInputStream(url, this);

    }
```

https://github.com/shannah/cn1-teavm-port/blob/bug-report-1/src/main/java/com/codename1/impl/html5/HTML5Implementation.java#L1574

If I run this, I get an exception

```
Exception: java.io.UTFDataFormatException - Malformed UTF-8 sequence
```

(The exception doesn't happen inside that method, but it happens later when processing the stream elsewhere).

If I change the method to:

```
 public InputStream getStream(String url){
        if (!isMediaResource(url)){
            return getArrayBufferInputStream(url);
        } 
        return null; //new MediaInputStream(url, this);

    }
```

https://github.com/shannah/cn1-teavm-port/blob/media/src/main/java/com/codename1/impl/html5/HTML5Implementation.java#L1574

It runs fine.

I have checked and the !isMediaResource(url) is always true for the current inputs.  I.e. the `return null` and `return new MediaInputStream(url, this);` lines are never reached.  Hence if the `null` version works, then so should the `return new MediaInputStream(url, this);` version.

I have two branches:
https://github.com/shannah/cn1-teavm-port/tree/media  (which is working)
and
https://github.com/shannah/cn1-teavm-port/tree/bug-report-1 (which has the problem)

The diff:
https://github.com/shannah/cn1-teavm-port/compare/media...bug-report-1

Since the actual error occurs later on, it is a bit tricky to debug.

